T1  - Trading Costs in Early Securities Markets: The Case of the Berlin Stock Exchange 1880–1910*
PY  - 2006
Y1  - 2006/01/01
DO  - 10.1007/s10679-006-9010-y
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 10
IS  - 4
SP  - 587
EP  - 612
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Based on daily prices (amtliche Kurse) we estimate effective spreads of securities traded at the Berlin Stock Exchange in 1880, 1890, 1900 and 1910. Several extensions of the Roll measure are applied. We find surprisingly tight effective spreads for the historical data, comparable with similar measures of the MDAX and DAX at the end of the 20th century.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1007/s10679-006-9010-y
